               <history>
                  <provenance when="1465">On fol. iii<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>‘Liber domus scolarium de Mertone ex dono Magistri <persName key="person_2898" role="dnr">Henrici Seuer</persName> sacre pagine professoris ac custodis eiusdem incathenatus ad communem usum sociorum in libraria studere uolencium Anno Domini M. CCCC. lxvi’. Faint marks near the foot of fol. 296 may be from the large brass chain-staple. </provenance>
                  <provenance>Seen at Merton by John Bale (Appendix C, no. 32). At the head of fol. 1 is the James no. ‘103’ (wrongly), s. xvii in. </provenance>
                  <provenance>Inside the front board is a sheet of paper with a table of contents and ‘F. 6, 8’ (canc.), s. xvii, and ‘O. 8. 2. Art:’, canc. and replaced with ‘G. 1. 6 (CLXXXVII)’ in red; the College bookplate.</provenance>
               </history>
